# App Development Standards

## Core Principles

All apps must be **premium, production-ready, and fully functional**. Quality is paramount.

## Design Requirements

- **Premium Quality**: Top-tier, class-leading design
- **User-Friendly**: Intuitive, easy-to-use interface
- **Professional Look & Feel**: Polished, modern UI/UX
- **Consistent Design**: Follow established design systems

## Functionality Requirements

- **Fully Functional**: Every feature must work completely
- **Optimized Performance**: Smooth, responsive operation
- **Production-Ready**: No bugs, errors, or incomplete features
- **Thoroughly Tested**: Tested across devices and scenarios

## API Integration

- **Cost-Friendly APIs**: Use affordable, efficient APIs
- **Optimized Usage**: Minimize API calls and costs
- **Error Handling**: Proper error handling for all API calls
- **Backend Integration**: Seamlessly integrate with provided backend

## Duplicate Management

When encountering duplicate apps:
1. **Keep**: The most complete, feature-rich version
2. **Discard**: All other duplicates
3. **Criteria**: Most features, best UX, most polished, fully functional

## Code Quality Standards

```typescript
// ✅ GOOD - Production-ready code
async function fetchUserData(userId: string) {
  try {
    const response = await api.get(`/users/${userId}`);
    return response.data;
  } catch (error) {
    logger.error('Failed to fetch user data', { userId, error });
    throw new UserFetchError('Unable to retrieve user data', { cause: error });
  }
}

// ❌ BAD - Incomplete, not production-ready
async function fetchUserData(userId: string) {
  const response = await api.get(`/users/${userId}`);
  return response.data; // No error handling
}
```

## Checklist Before Completion

- [ ] All features fully implemented
- [ ] Premium design implemented
- [ ] Fully optimized
- [ ] Backend integrated
- [ ] APIs cost-optimized
- [ ] No duplicates exist
- [ ] Thoroughly tested
- [ ] Production-ready

## App Purpose

Every app must do its intended purpose **exceptionally well**. If it doesn't serve its purpose perfectly, it's not ready.
